Date:  0/0/1922
Source:  Sheep Farming in NZ
Author:  PERRY
Vol / Page:  122
Edition:
Quote:  Rolling. - When the wool is opened at the sale it is in the best interests of the seller if the best and most attractive part of the fleece, viz., the shoulder, is exposed to view. ... There are many ways [123] of rolling, but two common ways are as follows:- (1) First throw in the neck so that it will rest on the shoulder and then turn in the two sides to the middle of the back. Commencing at the tail, roll the fleece towards the neck.
